    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before installing the auxiliary drive gear, the mainshaft must be completely installed.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, press the spacer into the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n7">Figure 237</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007n7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007n7" filename="../figg13/G13007N7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 237. Seat Bearing in Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the auxiliary bearing on the mainshaft up to the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n7">Figure 237</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a brass maul to seat the bearing in the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n7">Figure 237</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the splined washer on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n8">Figure 238</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007n8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007n8" filename="../figg13/G13007N8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 238. Install Splined Washer on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the retainer ring bolt holes with the tapped holes (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n8">Figure 238</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n9">Figure 239</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007n9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007n9" filename="../figg13/G13007N9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 239. Install Auxiliary Drive Gear and Retaining Washer on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts, and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n9">Figure 239</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary drive gear and retaining washer on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007n9">Figure 239</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary drive gear retaining snap ring in the mainshaft snap ring groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007o0">Figure 240</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007o0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007o0" filename="../figg13/G13007O0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 240. Install Auxiliary Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
